I need to identify the specific line item and value representing the amount of profit after all expenses have been deducted from total revenue.

Looking at the cash flow statement, I can see that "Net Profit" represents the amount of profit an entity retains after all expenses have been deducted. This is the first line item under "Cash Flow From Operating Activities" with a value of 112375.10.

The net profit is the bottom-line figure that shows what remains after all operating costs, interest, tax, depreciation, and amortization have been deducted from the total revenue.

{"solution": {'value': '112375.10'}}
